      "\n    all_goals\n      try { \n        have h1 : tâ‚پ.size < 2 ^ tâ‚پ.height := ihl\n        have h2 : tâ‚‚.size < 2 ^ tâ‚‚.height := ihr\n        have h3 : tâ‚پ.height â‰¤ max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height := by \n          cases max_cases tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height with\n          | inl h => \n            omega\n          | inr h => \n            omega\n        have h4 : tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height := by \n          cases max_cases tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height with\n          | inl h => \n            omega\n          | inr h => \n            omega\n        have h5 : 2 ^ tâ‚پ.height â‰¤ 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n          apply pow_le_pow_right \n          all_goals \n            try { \n              omega \n            } \n            try { \n              nlinarith \n            }\n        have h6 : 2 ^ tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n          apply pow_le_pow_right \n          all_goals \n            try { \n              omega \n            } \n            try { \n              nlinarith \n            }\n        have h7 : tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size < 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n          linarith \n        have h8 : 1 + tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size < 2 ^ (1 + max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n          have h9 : 1 + tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size < 1 + 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n            linarith \n          have h10 : 1 + 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) â‰¤ 2 ^ (1 + max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n            have h11 : 2 ^ (1 + max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) = 2 * 2 ^ (max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height) := by \n              ring \n            rw [h11] \n            nlinarith \n          linarith \n        linarith \n      }\n    all_goals\n      try { \n        omega \n      }\n    all_goals\n      try { \n        tauto \n      }\n    all_goals\n      try { \n        nlinarith \n      }\n  }",
      "e menor que k, para\nqualquer k natural.  Pelo lado direito temos que âŒˆlog(n-1)âŒ‰ <= k <=>\nn-1 <= 2^k.  Pelo lado esquerdo:\n\n    âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1)âŒ‰ + 1 <= k <=> âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1)âŒ‰ <= k-1,\n                                 <=> log(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1) <= k-1,\n                                 <=> âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1 <= 2^(k-1),\n                                 <=> âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> (n+1)/2 <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> n+1 <= 2^k + 2,\n                                 <=> n-1 <= 2^k.\n\nO que completa a prova, uma vez que ambos os lados chegam na mesma\nproposiأ§أ£o.\n\n-/\n\n\n/- 4.4 : see the book -/\n\n/-!\n# Exercicio 4.5\n\nIndexing the coordinates from zero, the positions are\n(0, 9), (5, 6), (7, 5), (9, 0)\n-/\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.6\n\n-- #eval D2.searchâ‚پ (خ» (x, y) => x ^ 3 + y ^ 3) 1729\n\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.7\n\nnamespace BST1\n\ndef flatcat : (t : Tree a) â†’ (xs: List a) â†’ List a\n| .null, xs => xs\n| .node l x r, xs => flatcat l (x :: flatcat r xs)\n\ndef Tree.flattenâ‚پ (t : Tree a) : List a :=\n flatcat t []\n\ntheorem flatten_eq_helper_accum (t : Tree a) (xs: List a)\n  : t.flatten ++ xs = flatcat t xs := by\n  induction t generalizing xs with\n  | null => rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [flatcat, â†گihr]\n    rw [â†گihl (x :: (r.flatten ++ xs))]\n    rw [List.append_cons]\n    rw [â†گ List.append_assoc]\n    rw [Tree.flatten]\n\nexample (t: Tree a) : t.flatten = t.flattenâ‚پ := by\n  induction t with\n  | null => exact rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [Tree.flattenâ‚پ]\n    simp [â†گ flatten_eq_helper_accum]\n\nend BST1\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.8\n\n\nnamespace BST1\n\nexample {خ± : Type} (t : Tree خ±) :\n  t.height â‰¤ t.size âˆ§ t.size < 2 ^ t.height := by\n  apply And.intro\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node tâ‚پ x tâ‚‚ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n     sorry\n  }\n  {\n  induction t with\n  | null => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n  | node tâ‚پ x tâ‚‚ ihl ihr =>\n    simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n    sorry\n```\n\nWe need to replace the `sorry` in the second part of the proof (the `t.size < 2 ^ t.height` part).\n\n```tactics\nimport Fad.Chapter4\nimport Fad.Chapter3\n\nnamespace Chapter4\n\n/- 4.2\nWe have smallest (a,b) = x such that f x < t â‰¤ f (x + 1)\nBut for t = 1024 and f x = x^2 below f x = t and f (x + 1) > t\n\n#eval D1.smallest (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 1024 (0, 1024)\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 32\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 33\n-/\n\n/- 4.3\n\nVamos provar por induأ§أ£o que\n\nT(x) = âŒˆlog(n-1)âŒ‰.\n\nPara o caso base (n=2)\n\nT(2) = âŒˆlog(2-1)âŒ‰ = âŒˆlog(1)âŒ‰ = âŒˆ0âŒ‰ = 0.\n\nSupondo valido para k < n, vamos provar para n. Como âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ < n,\nvale a hipotese de inducao, entao temos que provar que:\n\nT(n) = âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1)âŒ‰ + 1 = âŒˆlog(n-1)âŒ‰.\n\nPodemos mostrar por desigualdade indireta, mostrando que o lado\nesquerdo e menor que k se e somente o lado direito e menor que k, para\nqualquer k natural.  Pelo lado direito temos que âŒˆlog(n-1)âŒ‰ <= k <=>\nn-1 <= 2^k.  Pelo lado esquerdo:\n\n    âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1)âŒ‰ + 1 <= k <=> âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1)âŒ‰ <= k-1,\n                                 <=> log(âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1) <= k-1,\n                                 <=> âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ -1 <= 2^(k-1),\n                                 <=> âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> (n+1)/2 <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> n+1 <= 2^k + 2,\n                                 <=> n-1 <= 2^k.\n\nO que completa a prova, uma vez que ambos os lados chegam na mesma\nproposiأ§أ£o.\n\n-/\n\n\n/- 4.4 : see the book -/\n\n/-!\n# Exercicio 4.5\n\nIndexing the coordinates from zero, the positions are\n(0, 9), (5, 6), (7, 5), (9, 0)\n-/\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.6\n\n-- #eval D2.searchâ‚پ (خ» (x, y) => x ^ 3 + y ^ 3) 1729\n\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.7\n\nnamespace BST1\n\ndef flatcat : (t : Tree a) â†’ (xs: List a) â†’ List a\n| .null, xs => xs\n| .node l x r, xs => flatcat l (x :: flatcat r xs)\n\ndef Tree.flattenâ‚پ (t : Tree a) : List a :=\n flatcat t []\n\ntheorem flatten_eq_helper_accum (t : Tree a) (xs: List a)\n  : t.flatten ++ xs = flatcat t xs := by\n  induction t generalizing xs with\n  | null => rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [flatcat, â†گihr]\n    rw [â†گihl (x :: (r.flatten ++ xs))]\n    rw [List.append_cons]\n    rw [â†گ List.append_assoc]\n    rw [Tree.flatten]\n\nexample (t: Tree a) : t.flatten = t.flattenâ‚پ := by\n  induction t with\n  | null => exact rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [Tree.flattenâ‚پ]\n    simp [â†گ flatten_eq_helper_accum]\n\nend BST1\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.8\n\n\nnamespace BST1\n\nexample {خ± : Type} (t : Tree خ±) :\n  t.height â‰¤ t.size âˆ§ t.size < 2 ^ t.height := by\n  apply And.intro\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node tâ‚پ x tâ‚‚ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n     sorry\n  }\n  {\n  induction t with\n  | null => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n  | node tâ‚پ x tâ‚‚ ihl ihr =>\n    simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n    sorry\n```\n\nWe need to replace the `sorry` in the second part of the proof.\n\n```tactics\nimport Fad.Chapter4\nimport Fad.Chapter3\n\nnamespace Chapter4\n\n/- 4.2\nWe have smallest (a,b) = x such that f x < t â‰¤ f (x + 1)\nBut for t = 1024 and f x = x^2 below f x = t and f (x + 1) > t\n\n#eval D1.smallest (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 1024 (0, 1024)\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 32\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 33\n-/\n\n/- 4.3\n\nVamos provar por induأ§أ£o que\n\nT(x) = âŒˆlog(n-1)âŒ‰.\n\nPara o caso base (n=2)\n\nT(2) = âŒˆlog(2-1)âŒ‰ = âŒˆlog(1)âŒ‰ = âŒˆ0âŒ‰ = 0.\n\nSupondo valido para k < n, vamos provar para n. Como âŒˆ(n+1)/2âŒ‰ < n,\nvale a hipotese de inducao, entao temos que provar que:\n\nT(n) = âŒˆlog(âŒˆ(n+