2. `t.size = 1 + tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size` (the root plus the sizes of the left and right subtrees)

For the first part of the conjunction, `t.height â‰¤ t.size`:
- `1 + max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ 1 + tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size`
- This simplifies to `max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size`
- By the induction hypothesis, `tâ‚پ.height â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size` and `tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ tâ‚‚.size`
- So `max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ max tâ‚پ.size tâ‚‚.size` (since max is monotone with respect to â‰¤)
- But `max tâ‚پ.size tâ‚‚.size â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size` (since `max a b â‰¤ a + b` for non-negative a, b)
- Thus `max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size`
- Therefore `1 + max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ 1 + tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size` which is `t.height â‰¤ t.size`

