- Since `tâ‚پ.height â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size` and `tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ tâ‚‚.size`, we have `max tâ‚پ.height tâ‚‚.height â‰¤ max tâ‚پ.size tâ‚‚.size`.
- But `max tâ‚پ.size tâ‚‚.size â‰¤ tâ‚پ.size + tâ‚‚.size` is not necessarily true. For example, if `tâ‚پ.size = 1, tâ‚‚.size = 1`, then `max 1 1 = 1 â‰¤ 1 + 1 = 2` which is true. If `tâ‚پ.size = 2, tâ‚‚.size = 1`, then `max 2 1 = 2 â‰¤ 2 + 1 = 3` which is true.
